environment.model.locations

Class TestLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • environment.model.locations.TestLocation
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TestPump, TestShoppingArea, TestTill

    public abstract class TestLocation
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the test class for Location, It tests the:
    • Location.enter(RoadUser)
    • Location.returnToQueue(RoadUser)
    • Location.clone()
    All test classes for the subclasses of Location must extend from this. TestLocation(Location) describes how this test class is implemented in the testing subclasses.
    Version:
    02/05/2017
    Author:
    Joshua_Eddy
    See Also:
    Location

      • testLocation

        private Location testLocation
        A Location that will be assigned to as a concrete subclass. This allows the testing of all the common functionality of Location.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TestLocation

        public TestLocation(Location testLocation)
        This constructs an new TestLocation. Calling this constructor initialises the parameter Location as the Location that all the tests contained with TestLocation will be performed on as these are the basic functions of a Location.
        Parameters:
        testLocation - An instance of a subclass of Location for which these general tests will be performed.

    • Method Detail

      • testEnter

        public void testEnter()
        Tests the Location.enter(RoadUser) method. This method should accept a RoadUser and if it is;
        • Not NULL
        • Not already in this Location
        If the Location.maxQueueSize is gretater than zero then that will be tested also. If there is any additional functionality to this method in a subclass of location then this method should be overrided and called in the test subclass.

      • testMaxQueueSize

        private void testMaxQueueSize()
        Test the Location.maxQueueSize. If the Location.maxQueueSize is greater than zero then the testLocation must be shorter than value.
        See Also:
